===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|en|enm|set}}, {{m|enm|sette}}, from {{inh|en|ang|set|t=seat, place of residence, camp, settlement, entrenchment, stable, pen}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*set|t=seat}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*setÄ…|t=seat}}.

====Noun====
{{wp}}
{{en-noun}}

# A [[punch]] for setting [[nail]]s in [[wood]].
#: {{ux|en|nail '''set'''}}
# A device for receiving broadcast radio waves (or, more recently, broadcast data); a radio or television.
#: {{ux|en|television '''set'''}}
# {{alt form|en|sett||a hole made and lived in by a [[badger]]}}.
# {{alt form|en|sett||pattern of threads and yarns}}.
# {{alt form|en|sett||piece of quarried stone}}.
# {{lb|en|horticulture}} A small [[tuber]] or [[bulb]] used instead of [[seed]], particularly onion sets and potato sets.
# The amount by which the teeth of a [[saw]] protrude to the side in order to create the [[kerf]]. <!-- see [[WP:saw set]] -->
# {{lb|en|engineering}} A [[permanent]] [[change]] of [[shape]] caused by [[excessive]] [[strain]], as from [[compression]], [[tension]], [[bend]]ing, [[twist]]ing, etc.
#: {{ux|en|the '''set''' of a spring}}
#* {{quote-book|en|date=29 March 1986|author=w:National Transportation Safety Board|title=Aircraft Accident Report: China Airlines Boeing 747-SP, N4522V, 300 Nautical Miles Northwest of San Francisco, California, February 19, 1985|chapter=1.12 Wreckage and Impact Information|url=https://www.ntsb.gov/investigations/AccidentReports/Reports/AAR8603.pdf|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220710162138/https://www.ntsb.gov/investigations/AccidentReports/Reports/AAR8603.pdf|archivedate=10 July 2022|accessdate=10 July 2022|page=12|text=The wings were bent or set permanently 2 to 3 inches upward at the wingtips; however, the '''set''' was within the manufacturer's allowable tolerances.}}
# A [[bias]] of mind; an [[attitude]] or pattern of behaviour.
# {{lb|en|piledriving}} A piece placed temporarily upon the head of a [[pile]] when the latter cannot otherwise be reached by the weight, or hammer.
# {{lb|en|printing|dated}} The [[width]] of the [[body]] of a [[type]].
# A [[young]] [[oyster]] when first [[attach]]ed.
# Collectively, the [[crop]] of young oysters in any [[locality]].
# {{senseid|en|series or group}} A series or group of something. (''Note the similar meaning in {{l|en|set|Etymology 4, Noun|id=matching collection}}'')
# {{lb|en|colloquial}} The [[manner]], [[state]], or [[quality]] of setting or [[fit]]ting; [[fit]].
#: {{ux|en|the '''set''' of a coat}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=29 Dec 84|volume=12|number=25|journal=Gay Community News|page=7|author=Amy Hoffman|title=Dyke Detectives Solve Murder Mysteries|text=So much of our culture, hidden by necessity for so long, involves subtle codes and signals: the '''set''' of her shoulders, the sway of his hips.}}
# The [[pattern]] of a [[tartan]], etc.
# The [[camber]] of a curved roofing tile.
# The full number of [[egg]]s set under a [[hen]].
# {{lb|en|obsolete|rare}} That which is [[stake]]d; a [[wager]]; hence, a gambling game.
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Henry 5|I|ii|passage=We will in France, by God's grace, play a '''set''' / Shall strike his father's crown into the hazard.}}
